template(name="md_drawer__demo")
  .component-title MD Drawer
  p.docs
    | The MD Drawer demo involves the drawers on this site itself. The left
    | drawer is used as a menu for the component demos, while the right drawer
    | is used as a menu for the API pages. The responsive width for the left
    | drawer is 960px, while the responsive width for the right drawer is 1440px.
  p.docs
    | With the screen width under 960px, use the
    +md_icon(icon="menu" classes="inline-with-text")
    | button as a toggle for the left drawer. At and above 960px, the left
    | drawer will be docked with the header panel. Similarly, below 1440px,
    | use the
    +md_icon(icon="code" classes="inline-with-text")
    | button as a toggle for the right drawer. At and above 1440px, the right
    | drawer will be docked with the header panel.
  p.docs
    | On iOS devices in full-screen mode, and on Android devices, a swipe can be
    | used to open and close the drawers. For example, a right edge pan opens
    | the left drawer, and a left pan on the open left drawer closes it.
  p.docs The drawers on this site are generated using the following code.
  +doc_box(
    id="doc-box--md-drawer"
    id__tabs="md-drawer__tabs"
    tabs=tabs
    name__spacebars="md-drawer__spacebars"
    name__jade="md-drawer__jade"
    code__spacebars=code__spacebars
    code__jade=code__jade
    api_screen="MD Drawer API"
  )

