template(name="md_drawer__api")
  h2.api__title MD Drawer API
  .api__description
    p
      | An MD Drawer is a component that provides a drawer panel that is
      | initially hidden off-screen, but can slide horizontally on to the screen
      | to reveal its content. An MD Drawer must be used along with an MD Header
      | Panel with which it can dock and undock based on the screen width.
    p
      | A drawer can be toggled open/closed using an icon button with the
      | attribute
      code.inline data-drawer-toggle
      | . For example, the toggle button for the left drawer must have the
      | attribute
      code.inline data-drawer-toggle="left"
      | . Once this attribute is assigned, no additional code is required from
      | the package user to operate the drawer. Each such toggle button will
      | also be automatically hidden when its respective drawer is docked.
    p
      | Alternatively the drawer can be manually opened and closed by the
      | package user using the API methods described below.

